1. Finding the Address of an Arduino Pin
Each pin is controlled by three registers:

DDR (Data Direction Register) â†’ Sets pin as INPUT or OUTPUT
PORT (Port Register) â†’ Controls HIGH or LOW
PIN (Input Register) â†’ Reads pin state
ðŸ”¹ Example: Addresses of Registers in Arduino Uno (ATmega328P)

Register	Address	Function
DDRB	0x24	Controls PB0-PB7 (Pin 8-13)
PORTB	0x25	Sets HIGH/LOW for PB0-PB7
PINB	0x23	Reads state of PB0-PB7
DDRC	0x27	Controls PC0-PC6 (Analog pins)
PORTC	0x28	Sets HIGH/LOW for PC0-PC6
PINC	0x26	Reads state of PC0-PC6
DDRD	0x2A	Controls PD0-PD7 (Pins 0-7)
PORTD	0x2B	Sets HIGH/LOW for PD0-PD7
PIND	0x29	Reads state of PD0-PD7

--------------------------------------------------
//Printing Pin Register Addresses

#include <Arduino.h>  // Needed for Serial in a custom main()

int main()
{

    init();  // Required to initialize Arduino core
		
  	Serial.begin(9600);
      while (!Serial);  // Wait for Serial Monitor to open

    Serial.print("Address of PORTB: ");
    Serial.println((uint16_t) &PORTB, HEX);

    Serial.print("Address of DDRB: ");
    Serial.println((uint16_t) &DDRB, HEX);

    Serial.print("Address of PINB: ");
    Serial.println((uint16_t) &PINB, HEX);
   
    while (1);  // Prevent program from exiting
 }